Review Form
</h1>
<br/>
<p>
The review form consists of several fields:

    Article Score, a rating from 1 to 4 summarising your overall impression of the article. 
    
    1 – Champion, 2 – Favourable, 3 – Indifferent, 4 – Detractor
    
    Your expertise Level on the Article subject. 1 - Expert, 2 - Knowledgeable, 3 – Outsider
    
    Article Summary, proof to the authors and editors you have read and understood the articles contents 
    
    in order to count the review as fair.
    
    Structured Criticism of the article, highlighting what you deem to be bad points or plaguing issues within 
    
    the article that the author should address when revising their article.
    
    A comments section detailing minor inaccuracies to alert the author, such as typographical errors or grammatical 
    
    mistakes.
    
    Additionally, a field for comments to be sent privately to the Editor, detailing very poor work, plagiarism, or 
    
    other kinds of bad practice. The author will not see this.
